<section xml:id="Axiom_2">
    <title>Axiom 2 - Betweenness I</title>
    <introduction>
    </introduction>

<statement>

If distinct point <m>P</m>, <m>Q</m> and <m>R</m> are collinear then exactly one of the following statements are true:
<ol>


<li>
<m>P</m> is between points <m>R</m> and <m>Q</m>, denoted by <m>R</m>-<m>P</m>-<m>Q</m> or <m>Q</m>-<m>P</m>-<m>R</m>;
</li>

<li>
<m>Q</m> is between points <m>P</m> and <m>R</m>, denoted by <m>P</m>-<m>Q</m>-<m>R</m> or <m>R</m>-<m>Q</m>-<m>P</m>; or
</li>

<li>
<m>R</m> is between points <m>P</m> and <m>Q</m>, denoted by <m>P</m>-<m>R</m>-<m>Q</m> or <m>Q</m>-<m>R</m>-<m>P</m>.
</li>

</ol>

</statement>

